    "biography": "<p>The Minotaur stalks caverns and ruins, a towering beast 7 to 9 feet tall with a man’s form crowned by a bull’s head and hide. Driven by a ferocious temperament, it roams tunnels and mazes, preying on humans and attacking anything its size or smaller with relentless pursuit as long as its quarry remains in view.</p><p>In battle, it either gores and bites for [[/r 1d6 #Gore damage]] and [[/r 1d6 #Bite damage]], or wields a weapon—favoring spears, clubs, or axes—with a +2 damage bonus from its brute strength (e.g., [[/r 1d6+2 #Weapon damage]] for spear). When armed, it forgoes its natural attacks, relying solely on the weapon’s might.</p><p>Semi-intelligent, some Minotaurs wield tools, while rare, clever ones may cast spells. Roaming in bands of [[/r 1d6 #Minotaurs wandering]] or lairs of [[/r 1d8 #Minotaurs in lair]], they hoard modest treasures, their chaotic nature a constant threat in shadowed depths.</p><p><strong>Terrain:</strong> Cavern, Ruins</p>",
